9 (A) THERE IS A GUN VIOLENCE VICTIM RELOCATION PROGRAM WITHIN
10 THE VICTIM SERVICES UNIT.
11 (B) THE PURPOSE OF THE PROGRAM IS TO ASSIST IN THE RELOCATION OF
12 VICTIMS OF GUN VIOLENCE IN THE STATE TO ENSURE THE SAFETY AND WELL–BEING
13 OF THE VICTIM AND THE VICTIM’S FAMILY.
14 (C) THIS SUBTITLE SHALL BE LIBERALLY CONSTRUED AND APPLIED TO
15 PROMOTE ITS UNDERLYING PURPOSE.
16 5–903.
17 (A) (1) AN INDIVIDUAL MAY REQUEST PARTICIPATION IN THE PROGRAM
18 THROUGH THE VICTIM SERVICES UNIT.
19 (2) AN INDIVIDUAL IS ELIGIBLE FOR ASSISTANCE THROUGH THE
20 PROGRAM IF:
21 (I) THE INDIVIDUAL IS A VICTIM OF GUN VIOLENCE IN THE
22 STATE;
23 (II) 1. THE INDIVIDUAL EXPERIENCED THE VIOLENCE
24 WITHIN CLOSE PROXIMITY TO THE INDIVIDUAL’S HOME; OR
25 2. THE INDIVIDUAL LIVES IN CLOSE PROXIMITY TO A
26 PERSON WHO IS SUSPECTED TO HAVE CAUSED THE VIOLENCE; AND
27 (III) THE INDIVIDUAL DEMONSTRATES A NEED TO BE
28 RELOCATED FOR THE SAFETY OF THE INDIVIDUAL OR THE INDIVIDUAL’S FAMILY.

