11 5–904.
12 (A) THE VICTIM SERVICES UNIT SHALL ASSIST AN ELIGIBLE VICTIM
13 ACCEPTED INTO THE PROGRAM BY:
14 (1) RELOCATING THE VICTIM AND THE VICTIM’S FAMILY TO A SAFE
15 LOCATION;
16 (2) PROVIDING THE VICTIM WITH FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE FOR
17 MOVING EXPENSES, SECURITY DEPOSIT, AND RENT; AND
18 (3) PROVIDING OTHER SUPPORT SERVICES, INCLUDING
19 COUNSELING, LEGAL ASSISTANCE, JOB TRAINING, AND RESOURCES AND SERVICES
20 FOR INDIVIDUALS WITH DISABILITIES.
21 (B) THE VICTIM SERVICES UNIT SHALL:
22 (1) COLLABORATE WITH OTHER STATE AND LOCAL AGENCIES,
23 INCLUDING LAW ENFORCEMENT, HOUSING AUTHORITIES, AND SOCIAL SERVICES, TO
24 PROVIDE COMPREHENSIVE SERVICES TO VICTIMS UNDER THE PROGRAM;
25 (2) CONDUCT COMMUNITY OUTREACH IN ORDER TO EDUCATE THE
26 PUBLIC ABOUT THE PROGRAM AND TO ENCOURAGE VICTIMS OF GUN VIOLENCE TO
27 SEEK ASSISTANCE UNDER THE PROGRAM; AND
28 (3) WORK TO ENSURE THAT VICTIMS UNDER THE PROGRAM WHO ARE
29 RENTERS ARE PROTECTED FROM EVICTION OR FROM BEING DENIED RENTAL
30 HOUSING BASED ON THE VICTIM’S STATUS IN THE PROGRAM.
31 (C) THE VICTIM SERVICES UNIT SHALL ADOPT RULES AND REGULATIONS

